TY  - CONF
TI  - Ensuring large-scale semantic interoperability: The estonian public sector's case study
AU  - Haav, H.-M.
AU  - Kalja, A.
AU  - Küngas, P.
AU  - Luts, M.
T2  - Frontiers in Artificial Intelligence and Applications
AB  - E-services are built upon the exchange of information between several databases and institutions. The creation process of new e-services may be not an efficient one because the discovery, integration and reuse of appropriate information resources is time-consuming as the meaning of these information resources is not well-enough documented. In order to describe the meaning of information resources - being poured into hundreds of heterogeneous databases, distributed between several institutions - some coordination, principles, architecture and infrastructure are needed. This paper outlines proposed large-scale semantic interoperability architecture and its pilot implementation in the Estonian public sector's semantic interoperability initiative. © 2009 The authors and IOS Press. All rights reserved.
